parts.1:
Thank you for being a member of the Electronic Frontier Foundation! Your
EFF membership lasts for 12 months and you have the opportunity to
select a free gift every time you renew! If you are a monthly donor,
your membership lasts as long as you like, and you are eligible for a
member gift every 12 months. Contributions are tax deductible as allowed
by law. EFF is a U.S. 501(c)(3) organization, and our federal tax ID
number is 04-3091431.

Your contribution makes a significant difference in our ability to
defend your rights in the digital world whether that means standing up
for users in the courts, educating the public about dangerous laws, or
creating privacy-enhancing technologies. We are pleased to offer you a
few modest perks as a token of our thanks. This is a one-time email
notice and EFF will never share your information with partnering or
supporting organizations. Contact us at membership@eff.org if you have
any questions!

EFF MEMBER BENEFITS:

-EFF Online Rights bumper sticker (via print mail).

-EFF Member Card (via print mail).

-Digital Badges: Show your support on your blog, website, or in an HTML
email signature.
https://www.eff.org/files/2016/11/01/2017mb.png

-Discounts on Events: Receive discounts on General Admission to EFF
events! Choose the member price when purchasing tickets or show your EFF
Member card at the door. Watch for specific details in event invitations.

-Speakeasy Invitations: Get notified about informal members-only meetups
and drink ups with EFF lawyers, activists, and technologists in your area!

-EFF Online Shop Discount: Get 10% off purchases (Gift Memberships
excluded) at EFF's online store by using the discount code ALIQUID16 at
https://www.eff.org/shop.

PARTNER DISCOUNTS FOR EFF MEMBERS:

-LeanPub: Get a copy of Uncensored, an ever expanding collection of
essays on Internet freedom from many of its original innovators. Follow
this promo url: http://leanpub.com/uncensored/c/effdonor.

-Borderlands Books and Cafe: Borderlands is San Francisco's home for
science fiction, fantasy, and horror books. Present your EFF Member Card
and get a 10% discount on in-store purchases. Borderlands Cafe also
offers occasional EFF Member specials so be sure to stop by for some
reading time and a treat! http://www.borderlands-books.com

-Magnatune: Get an $8 gift card from Magnatune, the music download
service that isn't evil. All the music is DRM free and licensed under
Creative Commons. Musicians get 50%, you get to choose the price you
pay, and you're encouraged to share your purchased music with 3 friends.
Go to http://magnatune.com and use the gift code: 111801248707

-No Starch Press: Get a 30% discount on geektastic books that entertain
and/or instruct by using the code EFFMEMBER at http://www.nostarch.com.

-Take Control Ebooks: Get a 30% off by following this EFF member portal.
http://www.takecontrolbooks.com/?pt=EFF&cp=CPN80131EFF

-- 
Aaron Jue
EFF Senior Membership Advocate
membership@eff.org
